# Performance Patterns

## Database (N+1 Prevention)

```typescript
// Bad: N+1 queries
const tournaments = await this.repo.find();
for (const t of tournaments) {
  t.entries = await this.entryRepo.find({ tournament_id: t.id }); // N queries!
}

// Good: eager load relations
const tournaments = await this.repo.find({
  relations: ["entries", "entries.bot"],
});

// Good: query builder with join
const tournaments = await this.repo
  .createQueryBuilder("t")
  .leftJoinAndSelect("t.entries", "e")
  .where("t.status = :status", { status: "active" })
  .getMany();
```

## Pagination

Always paginate large result sets:

```typescript
async findAll(page = 1, limit = 20): Promise<[Tournament[], number]> {
  return this.repo.findAndCount({
    skip: (page - 1) * limit,
    take: limit,
    order: { created_at: "DESC" },
  });
}
```

## React Memoization

```tsx
// Memo for expensive pure components
const ExpensiveList = React.memo(function ExpensiveList({ items }: Props) {
  return items.map(item => <ExpensiveItem key={item.id} item={item} />);
});

// useCallback for handlers passed to children
const handleClick = useCallback((id: string) => {
  setSelected(id);
}, []);

// useMemo for expensive computations
const sortedItems = useMemo(() => 
  items.slice().sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score),
  [items]
);
```

## Avoid Inline Objects in JSX

```tsx
// Bad: creates new object every render
<Component style={{ margin: 10 }} options={{ sort: true }} />

// Good: stable references
const style = { margin: 10 };
const options = useMemo(() => ({ sort: true }), []);
<Component style={style} options={options} />
```

## WebSocket Events

Don't emit more than necessary:

```typescript
// Bad: emit on every state change
this.server.emit("gameState", fullState); // Every action!

// Good: emit targeted updates
this.server.emit("playerAction", { playerId, action, amount });
// Full state only on subscribe or significant changes
```

## Lazy Loading

Use dynamic imports for large pages:

```tsx
const AdminAnalytics = lazy(() => import("./pages/AdminAnalytics"));

<Suspense fallback={<Loading />}>
  <AdminAnalytics />
</Suspense>
```
